body:
I would like to help out with this issue. Can I please work on the following directories?

- pandas/core/dtypes/
- pandas/core/groupby/
- pandas/core/reshape/
- pandas/core/computation/

Hey @alexander-ponomaroff thanks for looking to contribute! I've put you down for dtypes and groupby first so we can concentrate on getting those merged first. Then we can look into the others. Let us know on here if you need any help.
Thank you very much @alimcmaster1 . I will start working on this as soon as possible.

@alimcmaster1  I will be working on:
```
pandas/tests/indexes/
pandas/tests/series/
pandas/tests/arrays/
pandas/tests/util/
```
thanks both @thoo and @pvarshney1729
@alimcmaster1 Do you want several PR from the same branch ?? I have more than 20 files.
I would recommend using separate branches so the PRs are independent of each other.
@alimcmaster1 That is what I think. Wait for more PR :) :)

Hi. I would like to help with this issue. May I work on those dirs?

- pandas/tests/extension/
- pandas/tests/io/parser/
- pandas/tests/io/formats/
- pandas/tests/groupby/

I would like to help out with this issue. I will be working on

- pandas/tests/indexing
so ok with more than 20 files, just don't go crazy, rather like to have logical groupings (like we have had already for some)

Sure @mwoss i've put you down for "pandas/tests/extension/" and "pandas/tests/io/parser/" focus on getting those two merged first. and thanks @amphy !

@alexander-ponomaroff - Mind if we wait to see if any other first time contributors are interested in taking a look - this issue has quite a low barrier to entry so it would be great to get as many new contributors as possible working on things! But if there is no response they are yours  :) Hope that makes sense!
@alimcmaster1 That's no problem, just let me know when I can start working on the other two directories if nobody new comes in.

I would also like to help with this issue, I'll be working on:

- `pandas/core/reshape/`
- `pandas/core/computation/`
- `pandas/tests/io/formats/`
- `pandas/tests/groupby/`
@streeck Do you mind if I have one of those directories since those are the only ones left?
Sure @sam-cohan, grab the last one: `pandas/tests/groupby/` ;)
Thanks!
Thanks both @sam-cohan and @streeck for looking to contribute! @streeck put you down initially for `reshape` and `computation` to give others the chance to contribute like i've said above. Thanks,
Thanks all for the contributions so far! Added few more sections - please comment on here if you would like to work on one

@thoo still some remain in the below sections - do you still want to work on these? Thanks for your efforts so far

( ive split up indexes )

pandas/tests/series/
pandas/tests/arrays/
pandas/tests/util/
@alimcmaster1  ~~Yes I can do them. Please assign me sections you want me to do.~~
@alimcmaster1 I had already submitted the PRs for those. #23344, #23347  and #23346. Let me know if I miss something.
@thoo there is still a few files under those sections - from looking at setup.cfg on master - let us know if you  still want to look at these.
@alimcmaster1  Sorry. I misunderstood the instruction. Those files are all good. `isort` did nothing on them but I will submit a PR to remove filenames from setup.cfg.
Still a few files to be worked on here if anyone is interested. Full list in [setup.cfg](https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/blob/master/setup.cfg), post on here if anyone is interested.
